-- Strauss Headed for Three-Week High on Accord With German Company
-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 2012-01-22T11:25:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-22/strauss-headed-for-three-week-high-on-accord-with-german-company.html
Strauss Group Ltd. (STRS)  was poised to
close at the highest level since Jan. 2 after its coffee unit
signed a five-year agreement with a German manufacturer to
produce coffee.  The  shares advanced  0.6 percent to 46.88 shekels at 1:07
p.m. in  Tel Aviv .  Strauss will have an option to buy the German company over
the course of the agreement based on a value of 53 million euros
($69 million), according to a  statement  filed to the Tel Aviv
Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
